snippet.title: Rebuilding Off-Grid Cabin & Digging Well at Alaskan Homestead
snippet.description:
I bought an abandoned Alaskan homestead and off-grid cabin with no water source or well. For 2 years I have been building roads, repairing buildings, fixing equipment and hauling water onto our property. For the next 3 months we are finishing some major projects and tackling our water problem. 

Check out our abandoned homestead playlist for all our homestead videos - 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL5EGD6MqjI6JeDJyJ6th8K9zI-mtYnYs9

snippet.title: Source to Sea down the River Thames WITHOUT Leaving it - Part 4
snippet.description:
Use: EDPRATTOB10 to get 10% off: https://oceanbottle.co/EDPRATTOB10 Each bottle funds the collection of 11.4kg of ocean-bound plastic!

Watch 'Part 5' early: (Just £2) https://www.patreon.com/edpratt OR on YT Memberships
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuNy42Y5egf07cSiHbF23wg/join

Donate to The Rivers Trust: https://www.justgiving.com/page/edprattriver

I’m attempting to travel from the source to the sea down the River Thames. That’s 210 miles of wading, swimming and kayaking along Britain’s busiest waterway. And to make things harder I’m doing the whole thing alone and self-supported.

Also, give Richard’s album some love. It's great! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ii7CktJ57s4 

Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/mredpratt
T-shirts: https://teespring.com/stores/edpratt

⛺GEAR USED
(Some of these are affiliate links. If you click through and make a purchase, I receive a commission at no extra cost to you)
- Waterproof backpack: http://bit.ly/4ifrjCZ
- Sawyer water filter: https://amzn.to/3Zo1XtP
- Petzl Headtorch: https://amzn.to/4gc2fea
- Alpkit: https://alpkit.com

📽 VIDEO MAKING GEAR:
- Insta360 X4: https://www.insta360.com/sal/x4?utm_term=INRVRQJ
- Insta360 X4 amazon: https://amzn.to/4fYSTmb
- GoPro: https://amzn.to/3D2jYX4
- Drone: https://amzn.to/4iiyUAt
- Power bank: https://amzn.to/4gmO5Xw

More about Ocean Bottle:
With the sale of each Ocean Bottle, 11.4kg of plastic (the equivalent of 1,000 ocean-bound plastic bottles) is collected globally, in coastal areas where plastic pollution is worst. They work with plastic collection partners Plastic Bank, Plastics for Change and Repurpose Global to actualise this collection. https://oceanbottle.co/pages/ocean-impact

This ad isn't intended to tell everyone watching to go out and buy an Ocean Bottle if you have a perfectly good reusable water bottle already. Quite the opposite - if your current bottle works, please keep using it. However, if your bottle is beyond repair, lost in the current or you’ve been meaning to start your reusable journey, choose an Ocean Bottle to make a difference.

Cartoon artwork: http://louisesaunders.artworkfolio.com

♫ SERIES MUSIC
Epidemic Sound: https://share.epidemicsound.com/mvwigl
